The paper deals with compressing deep convolutional neural networks for mobile applications, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses variational Bayesian matrix factorization, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses implementation issues related to convolutional operations, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
